CONTEXT
build_llm_for_model is passing api_key=False, causing a ValidationError.
The app constructs its LLM as:
    from app.core.config import settings
    ChatOpenAI(
        model=settings.AI_MODEL,
        base_url=settings.AI_API_URL,
        api_key=settings.AI_API_KEY,
        streaming=True,
    )

FIX
Rewrite build_llm_for_model and MODEL_OVERRIDES so that:
- By default, it uses settings.AI_API_URL and settings.AI_API_KEY
  from app.core.config (same as the app).
- Only the MODEL NAME changes per entry in MODELS_TO_TEST.
- MODEL_OVERRIDES is optional: if an entry provides base_url/api_key,
  use those (for testing an external paid model); otherwise fall back
  to settings defaults.

Implementation:

from app.core.config import settings
from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI

MODEL_OVERRIDES = {
    # "external-model-name": {
    #     "base_url": "https://api.anthropic-or-other.com/v1",
    #     "api_key": "sk-...",
    # },
}

def build_llm_for_model(model_name: str):
    override = MODEL_OVERRIDES.get(model_name, {})
    base_url = override.get("base_url", settings.AI_API_URL)
    api_key = override.get("api_key", settings.AI_API_KEY)
    return ChatOpenAI(
        model=model_name,
        base_url=base_url,
        api_key=api_key,
        temperature=0,
    )

Note: do NOT set streaming=True here (the agent executor doesn't need
it and it can complicate the callback capture). temperature=0 for
deterministic testing.

